Member Enumeration Documentation

enum ExternalSearchDescEntry::val_type_t
 

Types of fields. Don't forget to change in servers (e.g. XML).

Enumeration values:
string_type  Value can be a string.
number_type  Value can be a number.
choice_type  Value can be one of the values in m_subVals (enum).

Constructor & Destructor Documentation

ExternalSearchDescEntry::ExternalSearchDescEntry (  int  id,
const MC2String &  name,
val_type_t  type,
uint32  required
) 
 

Creates a new ExternalSearchDescEntry.

Parameters:
id The id to send back to the server together with the value.
name The text to display when showing this.
type The type of value. If choice_type, then there are choices in the vector of sub-values.
required Bitfield which is used to check if a value is required. It is done like so: uint32 x = MAX_UINT32; for ( i in filled_in_fields ) x &= i.value; for ( i in not_filled_in_fields && i.value != 0 ) x &= ~i.value; if ( x ) then all is ok.
